flowchart TD
    A([Start: Begin school day during initial 15-minute morning block]) --> B[Plug computer into charging area]
    B --> C[Log in to computer]
    C --> D[Open Gmail and log in]
    D --> E[Open ProgressBook and sign in]
    E --> F[Read subject lines for emails received 5:00-7:00 AM]

    F --> G{Coverage request email?}
    G -- No --> H[Proceed to Google Calendar check]
    G -- Yes --> I[Open coverage request email]
    I --> J{Is requesting teacher a high school teacher?}
    J -- No --> K[Do not cover and delete coverage email]
    J -- Yes --> L{Free from lab setup or teardown at that time?}
    L -- No --> K
    L -- Yes --> M{Prior knowledge of students for grades 9-11 only?}
    M -- No --> K
    M -- Yes --> N[Accept coverage]
    N --> O[Open coverage spreadsheet attached to email]
    O --> P[Click correct day of week]
    P --> Q[Record first initial and last name by bell you can cover]
    K --> H
    Q --> H

    H --> R[Open Google Calendar]
    R --> S{PLC meeting after school?}
    S -- Yes --> T[Write PLC reminder on whiteboard]
    S -- No --> U[No PLC reminder needed]
    T --> V{Lunch duty assigned?}
    U --> V
    V -- Yes --> W[Record lunch duty reminder on whiteboard]
    V -- No --> X[No lunch duty reminder needed]
    W --> Y[Create paper with 4 columns SH L PB AS]
    X --> Y

    Y --> Z[Mark through L column if lunch duty assigned]
    Z --> AA[Mark through AS column if PLC meeting scheduled]
    AA --> AB[List assignments to grade in PB]
    AB --> AC[List emails to send or respond in SH]
    AC --> AD[List positive communication home recipient in SH]
    AD --> AE[List lab related needs in SH and L]
    AE --> AF[List unexpected tasks in AS]

    AF --> AG[Study Hall email procedures and positive communication tasks]
    AG --> AH[Read SH note for student receiving positive communication]
    AH --> AI[Open Gmail compose]
    AI --> AJ[Open RHS Hub then Positive Communication feedback form]
    AJ --> AK[Open Google Drive then Parent Communication SP26 spreadsheet]
    AK --> AL[Click student bell tab]
    AL --> AM[Open ProgressBook gradebook and select bell]
    AM --> AN[Select student then Contact then copy parent email]
    AN --> AO[Paste parent email into new message]
    AO --> AP[Subject line student first name great day in science]
    AP --> AQ[Write positive behavior email and send]
    AQ --> AR[Update SP26 spreadsheet date format reason]
    AR --> AS[Complete Positive Communication Google form]
    AS --> AT[Read emails received 7:00-9:55 AM]
    AT --> AU[Respond to emails with specific requests]
    AU --> AV[Delete emails that do not require retention]

    AV --> AW[Lunch lab supply reset]
    AW --> AX[When students leave for lunch walk quick room lap for misplaced supplies]
    AX --> AY[Open lesson sequence file]
    AY --> AZ[Click daily lesson summary]
    AZ --> BA[Compare front table supplies with lesson summary list]
    BA --> BB{Supplies match lesson sequence list?}
    BB -- No --> BC[Get missing supplies from lab supply cabinet]
    BB -- Yes --> BD[No supply retrieval needed]
    BC --> BE[If supplies cannot be replaced document shortage on Wish List spreadsheet]
    BD --> BF[Proceed to Plan Bell]
    BE --> BF

    BF --> BG{Plan Bell day type}
    BG -- Monday-Thursday --> BH[Open ProgressBook gradebook]
    BH --> BI[Select bell]
    BI --> BJ[Select assignment]
    BJ --> BK{Assignment on Google Classroom?}
    BK -- Yes --> BL[Grade assignment for current bell]
    BK -- No --> BM[Alphabetize paper assignments by last name]
    BM --> BL
    BL --> BN[Enter grades in ProgressBook under selected assignment tab]
    BN --> BO[Repeat for each bell]

    BG -- Friday --> BP[Connect computer to second screen]
    BP --> BQ[Open ProgressBook gradebook]
    BQ --> BR[Select Bell 1 and weekly Snorkl assignment]
    BR --> BS[Open Snorkl and drag tab to second screen]
    BS --> BT[Snorkl classes Bell 1]
    BT --> BU[Verify submissions sorted by last name and highest score shown]
    BU --> BV[Enter 10 in ProgressBook for students scoring 3 or 4]
    BV --> BW[Play recordings for students scoring 1 or 2]
    BW --> BX[Score using rubric for 1s and 2s]
    BX --> BY[Enter 0 for non submissions]
    BY --> BZ[Repeat Snorkl grading steps for bells 2 3 6 7]

    BO --> CA[After School classroom reset]
    BZ --> CA
    CA --> CB[Walk a lap around room]
    CB --> CC[Remove items left in sinks]
    CC --> CD[Inspect eyewash stations turn off any running station return handle upright]
    CD --> CE[Count chairs at each table add chairs until each table has two]
    CE --> CF[Pick up trash]
    CF --> CG[Pick up pencils and store in desk container]
    CG --> CH[Return all supplies to cabinet]
    CH --> CI[Wash glassware as needed]
    CI --> CJ[Put next day supplies on front table]

    CJ --> CK{Any exceptions or contingencies encountered?}
    CK -- Required system unavailable --> CL[Defer affected task and reschedule]
    CK -- Parent contact not found --> CM[Record issue and notify administration]
    CK -- Grading incomplete --> CN[Carry remaining grading to next available time block]
    CK -- None --> CO([End: Day concludes with tasks completed deferred scheduled and classroom reset])
    CL --> CO
    CM --> CO
    CN --> CO
